CHIKUNGUNYA (40): INDIA
***********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 23 Sep 2008
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.hindu.com/2008/09/23/stories/2008092355991100.htm>


Chikungunya cases on the rise
-----------------------------
Chikungunya cases increased [in India], with the latest figures
touching 70 740 as against 59 536 last year [2007]. While Karnataka
tops with 48 618 cases, Kerala has reported 24 605 and Maharashtra 398.

Cases have also been reported from Gujarat, Andhra Pradesh, Goa,
Tamil Nadu, and Haryana.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This report indicates a large number of chikungunya virus infections
in India so far in 2008. It would be interesting to know how many of
these reported chikungunya cases were laboratory confirmed.

A map of India showing the location of the states mentioned above can
be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India can be accessed
at: <http://healthmap.org/promed?v=22.9,79.6,5>. - Mod.TY]
